// expect-fail: E1001
// expect-msg: column 18
//
// A line comment with no trailing newline must preserve the original
// start column when computing the EOF position (nexus-9w6l). With the
// buggy `col: 1 + l - p` formula the column is wrong (14 instead of 18)
// because it restarts from 1 instead of the comment's start column (5).
//
// The body below is `let // no newline` with no trailing newline.
// The `//` starts at column 5; after consuming 13 bytes to EOF the
// correct column is 5 + 13 = 18.  The error "expected identifier, got
// 'eof' at line 1, column 18" confirms the fix is in effect.
let // no newline